articles.content:
After approving and placing the stamp on the transport manifest, the municipality or county (city) competent authority shall reply to owners of toxic chemical substances online and notify the municipality or county (city) competent authority of where the transportation is destined.
Owners of toxic chemical substances shall distribute, receive and preserve approved and stamped transport manifests according to the following rules:
1. Submitted to transportation relevant organizations(agencies);
2. Preserved by owners of toxic chemical substances for future reference;
3. Given to the shipper of toxic chemical substances before the delivery;
4. Given to the consignee of toxic chemical substances before the delivery.
Where the transport manifest is declared in writing, owners of toxic chemical substances shall be liable to give the approved transport manifest to the municipality or county (city) competent authority where the transportation is destined.
